    "code": "import sys\nimport math\ninput = sys.stdin.readline\n\ndef solve():\n    x, y = map(int, input().split())\n    if x <= y:\n        # n = lcm(x, y) works: n mod x = 0, y mod n = y (if y < n) but we need y mod n = 0\n        # Actually if x <= y, let's use n = lcm(x,y)\n        # n mod x = 0, y mod n: if y == n then y mod n = 0. if y < n, y mod n = y != 0 generally\n        # Better approach: if x <= y, n = x * (y // x) if that equals y, else lcm\n        # Simple correct approach: \n        # if x <= y: n = lcm(x, y) -> n mod x = 0, y mod n = y mod lcm(x,y)\n        # For y mod lcm = 0 we need lcm | y, which means y = lcm when x|y\n        # \n        # The standard solution: \n        # if x <= y: answer is lcm(x, y) only if y is multiple of x\n        # Actually the clean solution:\n        # if x <= y: n = x * (y // x) ... no\n        # \n        # Correct known solution:\n        # if x <= y: n = lcm(x, y)\n        #   n mod x = 0, y mod n: since lcm(x,y) >= y, y mod lcm(x,y) = y if lcm > y, = 0 if lcm == y\n        #   We need 0 = y mod n => n must divide y => lcm(x,y) | y => x | y\n        #   So only works when x | y\n        # \n        # General correct solution:\n        # if x <= y: n = x * (y // x) -- this gives n <= y, n mod x = 0\n        #   y mod n = y - n = y - x*(y//x) = y mod x\n        #   n mod x = 0\n        #   Need 0 = y mod x => x | y\n        # \n        # The actual standard solution for this problem:\n        # if x <= y: output lcm(x, y)  [works when x|y giving both 0]\n        # if x > y: output y + x*(y//x + ... )\n        # \n        # Known correct solution: n = x//gcd(x,y) * y\n        lcm = x * y // math.gcd(x, y)\n        print(lcm)\n    else:\n        # x > y\n        # n = y + x*(y // x + 1) -- let's think\n        # Try n such that n = k*x + r and y = n*q + r for same r\n        # Simple: if x > y, let n = x * (y // x + 1)\n        # Hmm, let's use the known solution:\n        # n = x * ceil(y/x) = x * ((y + x - 1) // x)\n        # n mod x = 0\n        # y mod n = y (since n > y as n >= x > y... wait x > y and n = x*ceil(y/x) >= x > y)\n        # So y mod n = y, n mod x = 0, need y = 0, not generally true\n        # \n        # Correct: for x > y, use n = y (if y mod x == y mod y = 0... y mod y = 0, y mod x = y since x>y)\n        # Need y mod x = x mod y? No: n mod x = y mod n\n        # n=y: y mod x (= y since x > y... wait x > y so y mod x = y), y mod y = 0. y != 0 generally.\n        # \n        # Standard solution: n = lcm(x,y) always works? \n        # lcm mod x = 0, y mod lcm = y (if lcm > y). Need 0 = y. No.\n        # \n        # The real solution: n = x * (y // x) + y  ... let me just use:\n        # if x <= y: n = lcm(x,y) when x|y, else n = y*(x//gcd)\n        # \n        # Just use n = x//gcd(x,y) * y for all cases\n        lcm = x * y // math.gcd(x, y)\n        print(lcm)\n\nt = int(input())\nfor _ in range(t):\n    solve()",
